The Beijing 2022 Olympic Winter Games is proceeding well as China has taken effective anti-epidemic measures including the application of a closed-loop management system. This has set an example for the global fight against the COVID-19 pandemic, a U.S. health expert has said. In an online interview with China Media Group on Sunday, Kate Tulenko, director of IntraHealth International, a global health nonprofit based in the United States, said judged from the three different perspectives on evaluating the success of major sporting events in the face of COVID-19, the Beijing Winter Olympics performed very well.